race.comment: RUSSIAN SUMMER (9) ran on strongly but just failed to pick up the winner last start over 1250m at Cairns. He's back to his best and draws a decent barrier here. Hard to beat in a suitable race. SUPER TWENTY THREE (14) brings a nose defeat here in a 55 and keep Wiggins. Tumbles in weight and that brings him right into it. MELO MELO KAVA (10) has only had one blip in a string of narrow defeats. Has some weight relief and is a player in this contest. HOT TORQUE INVEGAS (12) races forward and spiked her figures winning in easier at Mackay. Carries 3kg less and holding the form she'd be a hope at a price.
